    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sodium chloride crystals prepared for use as a food seasoning and preservative. Table salt contains sodium chloride with small amounts of a free-flowing agent (calcium silicate or magnesium carbonate), an anti-caking agent (sodium ferrocyanide), an iodizing salt (potassium iodide or sodium iodide), and an iodide stabilizer (sodium carbonate and sodium thiosulfate).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
